<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-01-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-01-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="964" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d964">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Dudley</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-01-04"><hi rend="italic">January 4,
                                1900</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 220.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            No. 327 of the 6th ultimo, forwarding the United States copy of the
                            treaty providing for the extradition of criminals, signed by yourself
                            and the Peruvian minister for foreign affairs.</p>
                        <p>The same has been transmitted to the Senate to receive the advice and
                            consent of that body to its ratification.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>